<h2>Why We Built This</h2>
<p>Most discussions about moving abroad rely on anecdotes, personal opinions, or outdated cost-of-living comparisons. LeavingAmerica.co was built to provide a straightforward way to compare countries using public economic data instead of guesswork.</p>
<p>The purchasing power gap between US cities and most of the world is significant. We wanted to make that gap visible and measurable, using the same data sources that economists and policy analysts rely on.</p>

<h2>What We Do</h2>
<p>We combine purchasing power parity data from the World Bank with regional price data from the US Bureau of Economic Analysis to estimate how far your salary would go in 82 countries around the world. We also track quality of life metrics including safety, healthcare, happiness, pollution, internet speed, traffic, unemployment, and GDP growth for each destination.</p>
<p>Beyond the financial calculations, we show you practical information about each country including how easy it is to enter on a US passport, the local level of English proficiency, the tax system, and whether a digital nomad visa is available.</p>

<h2>Our Data</h2>
<p>Every number on this site comes from a publicly available, independently maintained source. We do not invent estimates or rely on user-submitted data. Our sources include the World Bank, the US Bureau of Economic Analysis, Numbeo, the World Happiness Report, the EF English Proficiency Index, and the Passport Index dataset.</p>
<p>Data is reviewed and updated quarterly using the latest publicly available figures from each source.</p>
<p>For a detailed explanation of how calculations and rankings work, see our <a href="/methodology">Methodology page</a>.</p>

<h2>Who Built This</h2>
<p>LeavingAmerica.co is an independent project built and maintained by a small team with a background in digital marketing and data analysis. We are not a financial advisory firm, immigration consultancy, or legal practice. LeavingAmerica.co is an independent project focused on economic data, purchasing power analysis, and international relocation research.</p>

<h2>What We Are Not</h2>
<p>We are not financial advisors, tax consultants, immigration lawyers, or relocation agents. The information on this site is for educational purposes only. Before making any major life decisions about moving abroad, please consult qualified professionals in the relevant fields.</p>

